# Theme: Boolean tests as history-preserving filters over the full packet space.
# Source: Boolean-algebra and test semantics from Section 2 of the paper.
# Property true-is-id: A universally successful test is skip.
# Property false-is-drop: A universally failing test rejects every history.
# Property conjunction-is-sequence: Two tests in sequence denote intersection.
# Property disjunction-is-choice: Choice between tests denotes union.
# Property excluded-middle: A test plus its complement accepts every packet.
# Property contradictory-ports: Distinct exact values for one header cannot coexist.
# Property restrictive-test-not-id: A single destination value excludes other values.
check true-is-id: filter(true) == id;
check false-is-drop: filter(false) == drop;
check conjunction-is-sequence: filter(dst_port = 80 & src_port = 50000) == filter(dst_port = 80) . filter(src_port = 50000);
check disjunction-is-choice: filter(dst_port = 80 | dst_port = 443) == filter(dst_port = 80) + filter(dst_port = 443);
check excluded-middle: filter(dst_ip = 192.0.2.1) + filter(!(dst_ip = 192.0.2.1)) == id;
check contradictory-ports: filter(dst_port = 80) . filter(dst_port = 443) == drop;
check restrictive-test-not-id: filter(dst_ip = 192.0.2.1) == id;
